[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is wonderful. The second version of LTX Director has just been released, which allows us to create videos using text, images, audio, video, and all at the same time.'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'LTX Director 2 is capable of performing INPAINT on audio, with the ability to extend videos forwards and backwards.'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It allows us to edit shots in RETAKE mode and much, much more. Put on your Film Director hat because you no longer have an excuse not to create videos with great control. Let\'s watch it!'

[00:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hello and welcome to a new video.'

[00:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I hope you like it a lot. Wait! What have you done to my eyes? The interface we\'re going to use is called ComfyUI. If you want to know how to install it, I\'ve included a link at the top. The LTX Director 2 nodes use the LTX 2.3 audio and video models.'

[01:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If you want to know more about this model, I\'ve included a link at the top. We\'ll start by updating ComfyUI to the latest version.'

[01:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We will do this by going into the Update folder and double-clicking on the Update_ComfyUI.bat file. Next, we will download the workflow.'

[01:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Once downloaded, we drag it into the ComfyUI workspace. Next, we will manually install the LTX 2 Director nodes. We will do this by entering the Manager and clicking on the Custom Notes Manager button.'

[01:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In the search box, enter the text What Dream and click on the Install button. The LTX Director node group may not install correctly due to the ComfyUI security level.'

[02:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If this happens to you, you should close ComfyUI and lower the security level to weak. If you don\'t know how to do it, I\'ve included a link at the top where I explain how to change this setting.'

[02:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Once ComfyUI is started, we repeat the procedure and this time we will be able to install this node. If we are missing any nodes, we must enter the Manager and then install the missing nodes.'

[02:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It is also recommended that we update all nodes by clicking on the Update All button. This is quite important because the official LTX nodes must be updated for LTX Director 2 to work.'

[02:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This workflow allows the use of models in Safetensors format or in GGUF format. Therefore, at this node you will have the option to download it in either of the two formats.'

[02:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If you are going to download the model in Safetensors format, you can choose between normal mode and distilled model. You will find it in different quantities.'

[03:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The model that is selected by default is the one I recommend. If we want to save resources, we should download the main model in GGUF format. We can select the main model in distilled format or in undistilled format.'

[03:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'As you already know, the higher the value followed by the letter Q, the higher the quality of the model, but it will consume more resources. We need to download the TEXT ENCODERS models, the VAE models, the time scaling model, and the distilled LoRA.'

[03:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'if you have selected a main non-distilled model. I have also added LoRA to this main node to increase the Omni-NFT-RL quality.'

[03:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In the lower download node, you have a collection of LoRAs IC. LoRA can make anyone cross-eyed.'

[04:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'A LoRA to improve movement, to increase detail. A LoRA to enable upscaling, to improve lip synchronization. A LoRA so that your video reacts to the audio you insert, so that the video generator has HDR.'

[04:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And a LoRA to improve the rendering of our video. If you want to know more about each of these LoRAs, you should visit their page on HuggingFace. To download any of these LoRAs, you must have a HuggingFace account.'

[04:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If you also have a HuggingFace download token, you can download them directly from this node. Once we have downloaded everything, we will refresh the browser and select the models we have downloaded in these nodes. Comenzando con el modelo principal, en formato Safetensors o en formato GGUF.'

[04:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If you are going to use the model in GGUF format, you must activate this switch. If you want to use the model in Safetensors format, this switch must be deactivated. If your main model is distilled, you will not need the distilled LoRA.'

[05:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'But if your main model is not distilled, then you must activate distilled LoRA. This part of the workflow is where the video generation takes place. It is made to the size indicated in this percentage, normally 50%.'

[05:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And in this other part is where the video expands to its final scale. In each of these parts we can adjust the sampling method, the scheduler and the number of steps among other settings. This workflow incorporates the frame interpolation system.'

[05:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We can turn it on or off with this switch. The first time you use it, it will automatically download the RIFE 47 rescaling model. If the template does not download, you will find instructions for downloading it manually in the description of this video.'

[05:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The recommended approach is to create an interpolation at double the frames per second, meaning 24 frames per second will become 48 frames per second. If you want to interpolate at three times the frames per second, you can adjust it at this node.'

[06:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If you are going to generate more than one video using the same settings, don\'t forget to change the seed or activate random mode. If the video you are generating is very long, you may encounter an out-of-memory error during the VAE decoding stage.'

[06:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You can activate VAE decoding in stages; we will do this by activating this switch. Whenever possible, it is best to use standard VAE decoding.'

[06:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In the LTX Director 2 node set we have this new node that allows us to see a preview of the video we are generating. In this first section we can enter a value to indicate the maximum resolution of the preview, which we see in JPEG format.'

[06:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We can increase or decrease the quality in this section, but as I said, it will only affect the preview. With this option we can enable or disable the standard ComfyUI preview.'

[07:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In this section we will adjust the number of frames we want to see in the preview. And in the next section we will indicate the speed shown in frames per second. This speed will only affect the preview.'

[07:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And now we move on to the most important node, the LTX Director node. In this node we can create our own timeline by adding elements such as images, texts, audios and videos. Our timeline will be composed of one or more of these types of elements.'

[07:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We can define the beginning of our timeline. In this section we will define the end with the value entered in this parameter. We can define the total duration with this other parameter.'

[08:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If we press the settings button we can change the representation of time indicated in seconds to its equivalent in frames. We will define the number of frames per second by adjusting this option.'

[08:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We can also adjust the width and height of the video we are going to generate. If we set these values ​​to zero, the measurement of the first graphic element entered will be taken automatically. Whether it\'s an image or a video.'

[08:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If the resolution of the entered elements is different from the resolution we have manually adjusted, we can decide in this section the resizing method. We can choose to maintain the same aspect ratio, compress to fit, fill with black space, fill with green space, or crop the image or video.'

[08:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We have three rows where we can add items.'

[08:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The main row, the audio row, and the video row for IC-type LoRA operations. If we add text, it will act as a prompt for the time period we specify.'

[09:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
